New in 0.4.0 [2013-10-23]:

* C++11 binding

  - Switch over to std::shared_ptr based Object implementation. The generated
    C++ code is not compatible with the ones generated by esidl 0.3.3 or
    earlier.

* The manual page for esidl

  - esidl.1 is generated from the new --help command line option

* Drop JSAPI and V8 bridge examples; please see the Escudo web browser for
  how to use the generated code with SpiderMonkey and V8.

* Drop NPAPI support

* Support Ubuntu 13.10

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

New in 0.3.3 [2013-09-16]:

* Support Ubuntu 13.10 Beta 1

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

New in 0.3.2 [2013-09-07]:

* C++11 binding

  - Fix not to use special operations for named operation invocations

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

New in 0.3.1 [2013-04-13]:

* Support Mac OS X Lion/Mountain Lion

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

New in 0.3.0 [2013-01-11]:

* Web IDL Core

  - Support 'Data?', 'ByteString', 'unrestricted float' and 'unrestricted double'
  - Support partial dictionary definitions

* C++11 binding

  - Map [Constructor] to a static class function named 'construct'
  - Map 'unrestricted float' and 'unrestricted double' to float and double
  - Map 'ByteString' to std::u16string
  - Generate string const references for arguments of enum types

* Support Fedora 18

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

New in 0.2.2 [2012-12-14]:

* C++11 binding

  - Generate string const references for function arguments
  - Generate dispatch() using Any::toArrayIndex for accessing indexed properties

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

New in 0.2.1 [2012-12-01]:

* C++11 binding

  - Fixed bugs around special operations

* Support Ubuntu 12.10

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

New in 0.2.0 [2012/07/01]:

* Web IDL Core

  - Support static operations, enumerations, union types, callback functions,
    and partial interface definitions

* C++11 binding

  - Support new message-oriented C++11 Web IDL binding based on duck typing
  - Generate string const references for function arguments
  - Map union types to Any
  - Map callback function to functors

* Included bridges for JSAPI and V8

* Support Fedora 17

